Using `groupby`, introduced in Drools `8.41.0.Final`, this is now possible:

```
rule &quot;Sum account amount by name&quot;
when
    groupby(
        $account: /accounts;
        $name: $account.name;
        $total: sum($account.amount)
    )
then
    System.out.println(&quot;Account &quot; + $name + &quot; has a total of &quot; + $total);
end
```

(the example given use the OOPath syntax, but the [traditional syntax is also supported][1])


  [1]: https://docs.drools.org/8.39.0.Final/drools-docs/docs-website/drools/language-reference/index.html#new-and-traditional-syntax_drl-rules

